SIMPLE: serge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serge
<hw>Serge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>serge</ets>,
<ets>sarge</ets>, <ets>originally</ets>, <ets>a silken stuff</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>serica</ets>, f. or neut. pl. of <ets>sericus</ets> silken. See
<er>Sericeous</er>, <er>Silk</er>.]</ety> <def>A woolen twilled stuff,
much used as material for clothing for both sexes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silk serge</b></col>, <cd>a twilled silk fabric used
mostly by tailors for lining parts of gentlemen's coats.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Serge
<hw>Serge</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>cierge</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
large wax candle used in the ceremonies of various churches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sergeancy</ent>⟦br⟧
